ploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-750x858.png" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-750x858.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1090x1247.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-210x240.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-768x879.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1343x1536.png 1343w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1790x2048.png 1790w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash.png 1958w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="73041" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/10/nyt-flash-based-visualizations-work-again/nyt-web-based-flash/" data-orig-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash.png" data-orig-size="1958,2240" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="NYT web-based Flash" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-750x858.png" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1090x1247.png" /></a></p>在 2000 年代，如果您想为……制作交互式或动画可视化<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/archive/" rel="tag">档案</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/flash/" rel="tag">闪存</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/new-york-times/" rel="tag">纽约时报</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/10/nyt-flash-based-visualizations-work-again/"><img width="750" height="858" src="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-750x858.png" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-750x858.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1090x1247.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-210x240.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-768x879.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1343x1536.png 1343w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1790x2048.png 1790w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash.png 1958w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="73041" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/10/nyt-flash-based-visualizations-work-again/nyt-web-based-flash/" data-orig-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash.png" data-orig-size="1958,2240" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="NYT web-based Flash" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-750x858.png" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/NYT-web-based-Flash-1090x1247.png" /></a></p><p>在 2000 年代，如果您想为网络制作交互式或动画可视化，Flash 是主要选择。当 Flash 失去支持并从互联网上消失后，长达十年的出色可视化不再有效。</p><p> 《纽约时报》使用 Flash 模拟器恢复了他们的档案。因此，那些被归入静态缩略图的作品又回来了。查看曾经让许多人感到不安的<a href="https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/interactive/2008/02/23/movies/20080223_REVENUE_GRAPHIC.html">票房流图</a>、显示像您这样的人的失业率<a href="https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/interactive/2009/11/06/business/economy/unemployment-lines.html">的多线图</a>，以及显示人们如何度过一天的<a href="https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/interactive/2009/07/31/business/20080801-metrics-graphic.html">交互式堆积面积图</a>。</p><p>我不知道 NYT 使用什么作为模拟器，但我猜它类似于开源<a href="https://ruffle.rs">Ruffle</a> 。我希望其他新闻媒体也能跟进。很高兴看到我最喜欢的可视化再次发挥作用。 [来自<a href="https://eagereyes.org/blog/2024/nytimes-web-flash-player">EagerEyes</a> ]</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/archive/" rel="tag">档案</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/flash/" rel="tag">闪存</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/new-york-times/" rel="tag">纽约时报</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73040</post-id></item><item><title>带收据打印机的地图</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/09/map-with-a-receipt-printer/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Tue, 09 Jan 2024 09:16:03 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Maps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Aaron Koelker]]></category><category><![CDATA[receipt]]></category><category><![CDATA[river]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73032 </guid><description><![CDATA[Aaron Koelker used a receipt printer to print a six-foot long map of&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/aaron-koelker/" rel="tag">亚伦·科尔克</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/receipt/" rel="tag">收据</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/river/" rel="tag">河</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="73033" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/09/map-with-a-receipt-printer/map-with-receipt-printer/" data-orig-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Map-with-receipt-printer.png" data-orig-size="726,1142" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Map with receipt printer" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Map-with-receipt-printer.png" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Map-with-receipt-printer.png" src="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Map-with-receipt-printer.png" alt="" width="726" height="1142" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-73033" style="max-width:400px;height:auto" srcset="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Map-with-receipt-printer.png 726w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Map-with-receipt-printer-210x330.png 210w" sizes="(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px" /></p><p>亚伦·科尔克 (Aaron Koelker) 使用收据打印机打印了一张六英尺长的佛罗里达州瓦库拉河地图。他概述了<a href="https://aaronkoelker.com/wakulla-receipt-map/">使用 Adob​​e Illustrator 和打印机的过程</a>。我现在想要一台热敏打印机。</p><p>另请参阅： <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2019/05/07/remixing-the-grocery-receipt-with-data-visualization/">带有图表的杂货收据</a>。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/aaron-koelker/" rel="tag">亚伦·科尔克</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/receipt/" rel="tag">收据</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/river/" rel="tag">河</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73032</post-id></item><item><title>抛硬币可能会倾向于它们开始的同一面</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/08/coin-flips-might-tend-towards-the-same-side-they-started/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Mon, 08 Jan 2024 10:51:24 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Statistics]]></category><category><![CDATA[bias]]></category><category><![CDATA[coins]]></category><category><![CDATA[František Bartoš]]></category><category><![CDATA[Scientific American]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73026 </guid><description><![CDATA[The classic coin flip is treated as a fair way to make decisions,&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/bias/" rel="tag">偏见</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/coins/" rel="tag">硬币</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/frantisek-bartos/" rel="tag">弗兰蒂塞克·巴托什</a>, <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/scientific-american/" rel="tag">《科学美国人》</a></p> ]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>经典的抛硬币被视为一种公平的决策方式，假设每次抛硬币正面或反面的机会均等。然而，František Bartoš 出于好奇，招募了朋友和同事，记录了超过 350,000 次翻转。<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.04153">似乎有一点点偏差</a>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/scientists-destroy-illusion-that-coin-toss-flips-are-50-50/">Shi En Kim 为《科学美国人》报道</a>：</p><blockquote><p>根据 arXiv.org 上发布的预印本研究结果显示，50.8% 的情况下，硬币落地时与抛掷之前相同的一面朝上。大量的抛出让统计学家得出结论，近 1% 的偏差并非侥幸。 “我们可以非常确定，在这个数据集之后，抛硬币存在偏差，”巴托什说。</p></blockquote><p>这里可能有不止一个警告，但即使有很多翻转，它们也只来自 48 个人，而且不同翻转者的偏见各不相同。</p><p>当然，如果你想得到对你有利的电话，也许可以尝试看看哪一方获胜并做出相应的选择。不会受伤。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/bias/" rel="tag">偏见</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/coins/" rel="tag">硬币</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/frantisek-bartos/" rel="tag">弗兰蒂塞克·巴托什</a>, <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/scientific-american/" rel="tag">《科学美国人》</a></p> ]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73026</post-id></item><item><title> 2023 年基于人工智能的事物</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/01/05/ai-based-things-in-2023/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Fri, 05 Jan 2024 09:28:50 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Statistics]]></category><category><![CDATA[AI]]></category><category><![CDATA[Large Language Model]]></category><category><![CDATA[Simon Willison]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=73022 </guid><description><![CDATA[There were many AI-based things in 2023. Simon Willison outlined what we learned&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/ai/" rel="tag">人工智能</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/large-language-model/" rel="tag">大语言模型</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/simon-willison/" rel="tag">西蒙·威利森</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> 2023 年有很多基于人工智能的事物<a href="https://simonwillison.net/2023/Dec/31/ai-in-2023/">。Simon Willison 概述了我们在这一年中学到的东西</a>：</p><blockquote><p>今年我们了解到的关于法学硕士的最令人惊讶的事情是，它们实际上很容易建立。</p><p>直觉上，人们会期望如此强大的系统需要数百万行复杂的代码。相反，事实证明几百行 Python 确实足以训练一个基本版本！</p><p>最重要的是训练数据。您需要大量数据才能使这些事情发挥作用，而训练数据的数量和质量似乎是最终模型的好坏的最重要因素。</p></blockquote><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/ai/" rel="tag">人工智能</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/large-language-model/" rel="tag">大语言模型</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/simon-willison/" rel="tag">西蒙·威利森</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 73022 </post-id></item></channel></rss><!-- *´¨)
